  • Classes in sep.gaia.resources used by sep.gaia.resources 
    Class and Description
    AbstractLoaderWorker
    A thread processing a part of a query in order to take e.g. advantage of higher bandwidth-usage.
    Cache
    A class for keeping resources in memory and accepting requests for them.
    DataResource
    Least common denominator of all resources in GAIA.
    DataResourceManager
    This class is an abstract class for all object to be managed.
    LoaderEventListener
    An interface for reacting if the corresponding loader has partially processed a query and therefore new data is avaliable.
    NotADummyException
    A exception that is thrown if a passed DataResource object unexpectedly does not have the dummy-flag set.
    Query
    Describes a query to be performed by a loader (s.
    QuerySplitter
    Interface accepted by Loader for splitting a query into pieces in order to process them asynchronously.
    ResourceMaster
    This class holds all DataResourceManager implementations.
    ResourceObservable
    A ResourceObservable is observed by a ResourceObserver implementation.
    ResourceObserver
    Interface which is implemented by resource-observing classes like the ResourceAdapter class.
    WorkerFactory
    Class for generating new workers.
